    <statement><p>Calculate the following. Use an improper fraction in your answer.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\frac{ \frac{2}{3} - \frac{3}{5} }{ \frac{5}{2} } =}</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>{\frac{2}{75}}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To simplify a complex fraction, we find the common denominator of all fractions. In this case, it is <m>30</m>. We multiply the complex fraction<rsq/>s numerator and denominator by this common denominator, and we have:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   \frac{ \frac{2}{3} - \frac{3}{5} }{ \frac{5}{2} } 
      \amp = \frac{(\frac{2}{3}-\frac{3}{5})\cdot 30}{ \frac{5}{2} \cdot 30 } \\
      \amp = \frac{\frac{2}{3} \cdot 30 - \frac{3}{5} \cdot 30}{ \frac{5}{2} \cdot 30 } \\
      \amp = \frac{20 - 18}{75 } \\
      
      \amp = {{\frac{2}{75}}}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Here is a simple way to do fraction multiplication:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ \frac{2}{3} \cdot 30 = 30 \div 3 \cdot 2 = 20 }</m></p>
</solution>
